Title: big or small, market leader or niche player?

Author: brlewis
Content: If you choose a problem to solve where the customers move slowly, you actually have an advantage over a 23-year-old working 16 hours a day.  With infrequent customer feedback, it's hard for the young startup to capitalize on all that free time, and it can burn through its cash waiting for feedback and growth.
